  "notes": "nghĩ = to think. It’s the basic verb for having thoughts or opinions in your head.\n\nUse it for thinking about something, considering something, or having an opinion.  \n\nYou’ll also hear nghĩ đến when something comes to mind. Suy nghĩ is similar but feels a bit deeper or more serious (like “to reflect”), while tưởng is “to mistakenly think.”",
